{
  "stem": "3012.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know because then the train must have pulled to the side spur to Birkenau because it made it easier for them to put the people-- to take the people off the train and just separate everybody.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then to the left was the Birkenau gas chamber and crematoria.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So instead of stopping at Auschwitz station, the train, after a while, pulled into Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I think that at Auschwitz station I must have seen a clock.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I believe-- well I can see the clock, but I cannot place it, where I saw it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That's, that's the problem.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I believe it showed 7:20 AM, I think.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I'm positive it was on the 15th of June, 1944.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They opened up the bolts, and just before they opened the bolts-- during the journey, somebody went into labor and was giving birth just as they unlocked the bolts.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was, along with the baby, the first person they took away.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All this upheaval on the station, and so many people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, and, and first we saw that they are what you would call here red caps.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The people in striped suits running around and yelling and screaming in German, get off the plane, leave everything there because it will be delivered to you later.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "From then on, I think we became totally disoriented-- totally.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as we got off the train and walked a few steps, they started separating us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My aunt, Olga-- who is in New York-- was with Grandma.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was with my father and my mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the person separated Aunt Olga from Grandmother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And my father-- I can see them, they are here.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] They were pushed to the left as we started walking.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
